$$\begin{cases}
p^2 - q^2 = 2 \\
p - q = 4
\end{cases} \underset{\text{add}}{\implies} p^2 - 2p - 2 = 0$$
Solving via the quadratic formula yields $p = 1 + \sqrt{3}$.  $$\therefore \begin{cases}
p = 1 + \sqrt{3} \\
